Absolute frequency of the target variable.

sum(data$CARAVAN == 1) / nrow(data)

The categories of the target variable are higly unbalanced, the ratio is 1:19 for the value 1.

num_vars <- c("MAANTHUI", "MGEMOMV")
par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
for (var in num_vars) {
  hist(data[, var], main = var, xlab = var, las = 2)
}

Plot of the distribution of the numerical variables

par(mfrow = c(1, 1))
cat_vars <- setdiff(names(data), num_vars)
for (var in cat_vars) {
  barplot(table(data[, var]), main = var, xlab = var, las = 3)
}

Plot of the distribution of the numerical variables
